# Design system enforcement

**Canonical summary:** **`AGENTS.md` §7 Design system**. This rule adds TS/TSX/CSS/MD-glob detail for editors; do not contradict the contract file.

## Design token contract

- Use design-system exports from `#lib/design-system` for:
  - preferred primitive aliases (`ui.radius`, `ui.padding`, `ui.gap`, `ui.elevation`, `ui.tone`, `ui.priority`)
  - geometry (`uiRadius`)
  - elevation (`uiSurfaceElevation`)
  - density / surface inset (`uiDensity`, `uiSurfaceInset`, `uiSurfaceSpaceKeys`)
  - typography / tracking (`uiTitle`, `uiTracking`)
  - semantic variants (button, badge, card schemas)
- Do not introduce raw geometry utilities such as:
  - `rounded-3xl`, `rounded-4xl`, `shadow-2xl`, arbitrary `rounded-[...]`, arbitrary shadow systems
- Spacing rhythm utilities (`p-*` / `m*` / `gap-*` / `space-[xy]-*`) must come from the token scale: Tailwind's spacing scale, `p-surface-*` / `gap-surface-*` (`--space-surface-*`), or `gap-density-*` (`--density-*`). Arbitrary literals (`p-[12px]`, `gap-[7px]`, `ml-[3.25rem]`) are forbidden; CSS-variable references (`var(--…)` / `--spacing(var(--…))` / `calc(var(--…)*…)`) remain allowed. Positioning (`top-[…]`, `inset-[…]`) and sizing (`w-[…]`, `h-[…]`) are out of scope.
- Exceptions must be explicitly allowlisted in `scripts/check-design-contract.mjs`.
- **`@theme inline`** in `app/globals.css` must only reference `var(--*)` names that exist under `:root` or `.dark` (checked by `check-design-contract.mjs`).

## Semantic color contract

- Semantic colors are defined centrally in `app/globals.css`.
- Components must consume semantic tokens: `bg-primary`, `text-muted-foreground`, `border-border`, etc.
- **Primitives:** use solid hover tokens (`bg-primary-hover`, `bg-secondary-hover`), not `hover:bg-primary/…` or `hover:bg-secondary/…` on filled actions (enforced in `check-design-contract.mjs`).
- Avoid hardcoded color values in components unless explicitly approved.

## Primitive ownership contract

- UI primitives are owned by `components/ui/**`.
- Application shell and ERP modules (`lib/features/**`) must import primitives only from `#components/ui/*`.

Forbidden outside `components/ui` (ESLint + policy):

```txt
@radix-ui/*
radix-ui
@base-ui/react
```

Deep imports of another module's internals (`#features/other/data/...`) remain forbidden outside that module; same-module paths are handled by `scripts/check-agent-contract.mjs`.

## Runtime validation contract

When variants, sizes, themes, or appearance values originate from JSON, CMS, query params, APIs, or external payloads — validate using exported schemas / parsers from `#lib/design-system`:

```ts
import {
  buttonVariantSchema,
  buttonSizeSchema,
  badgeVariantSchema,
  cardSizeSchema,
  uiPrimitiveSchema,
  parseUiSurfaceSpaceKey,
  parseSurfaceElevation,
} from "#lib/design-system"

buttonVariantSchema.parse(value)
uiPrimitiveSchema.parse(payload.primitive)
parseUiSurfaceSpaceKey(payload.inset)
```

## Material semantics (shell adoption)

- **Authority:** `app/globals.css` (`.af-material-*`, blur/saturation tiers), **ADR-0001 §13**, **`.cursor/rules/material-semantics.mdc`**, mechanical drift in **`scripts/check-design-contract.mjs`**.
- **Runtime validation:** when `data-phase` / `data-lynx` comes from JSON, query params, or CMS — use **`parseUiMaterialPhase`** / **`parseUiLynxState`** from **`#lib/design-system`** (canonical strings only; matches CSS attribute selectors).
- **Do not** export or duplicate material class strings from TS — phases are driven by stable base classes + `data-*` attributes.
- **Do not** use Tailwind arbitrary blur (`blur-[…]`, `backdrop-blur-[…]`) or JSX `backdropFilter` / `willChange` — CI rejects them outside `app/globals.css`.

## Anti-drift rules

- Prefer existing design-system patterns over introducing new visual abstractions.
- Prefer familiar primitive aliases (`card`, `panel`, `dialog`, `popover`, `toolbar`, `table`) through `ui.*`; keep product philosophy in behavior, not visual class names.
- Do not create parallel token systems or local shadow/radius scales.
- Keep visual language structurally consistent across ERP modules.

## Documentation sync (`docs/design-system/**/*.md`)

Applies when editing **`docs/design-system/**/\*.md`\*\*.

- **Code is truth:** [`app/globals.css`](../../app/globals.css), [`lib/design-system.ts`](../../lib/design-system.ts), [`components/ui/`](../../components/ui/). Docs describe what code implements, never ahead of it.
- Do not document Figma names, variant strings, or CSS variables that are **not** implemented in code and `lib/design-system.ts`.
- When tokens or primitive APIs change, update **`docs/design-system/governance.md`** (Figma notes) or Code Connect templates beside primitives, in the **same** change when your team maintains them.
- For class-level UI rules (radius, semantic colors, hover tokens), follow the sections above — same source of truth.

## CI

Before merge, keep all checks green:

```bash
pnpm lint       # includes check-agent-contract.mjs + check-design-contract.mjs
pnpm typecheck
```
